From 4a7e7f3af725bac218a2bf5f9ae5638846710126 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sanket Bumb <sanket@yourowncrm.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 12:48:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: payment enum mismatch, dialog positioning, label
 clutter, customer name header
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Payment posting failure (400 / looked like CORS) — root cause fixed:
- Frontend payment dropdowns (Quick Pay + Billing > Payments) have always
  offered 5 method options: CARD, CASH, CHECK, TRANSFER, OTHER
- Backend PaymentMethod Java enum only recognized 4: CASH, CARD, ONLINE,
  CHECK — selecting TRANSFER or OTHER caused Jackson to fail
  deserializing the request body into the enum BEFORE validation even
  ran, surfacing as a 400 that looked like a CORS failure in the browser
- Database payment_method ENUM type had the same 4-value restriction
- Fixed both: PaymentMethod.java now has CASH/CARD/CHECK/TRANSFER/OTHER;
  V6 migration adds TRANSFER and OTHER to the Postgres enum type
  (ONLINE kept for backward compat with any existing rows, just unused
  going forward)

Collect Payment dialog positioning — reverted to the working pattern:
- A previous change made collectPayment() open QuickPayDialogComponent
  ON TOP of the still-open appointment dialog (to support an inline
  'Paid .xx' label) — this reintroduced the exact 'renders at bottom
  of page' bug that was previously fixed for Visit Notes/Logs/All Visits
- Restored the close-then-reopen-centered pattern: save appointment,
  close this dialog, open QuickPay centered, then after QuickPay closes,
  reopen THIS SAME appointment dialog (centered) with fresh data so the
  'Paid .xx' button state is preserved across the round-trip
- Documented a known minor gap: if the user edits and re-saves from the
  reopened dialog, the schedule grid's auto-refresh doesn't re-fire for
  that second save (no listener wired to the nested reopen) — the first
  save's refresh (showing the payment-related changes) still happens
  correctly

Appointment dialog — UI cleanup:
- Removed the confirmation sub-labels (with redundant ✕ clear buttons)
  that appeared below Location, Visit Type, and Visit Status after
  selection — the search input itself already displays the selected
  name, so the sub-label was duplicate information
- Reduced vertical spacing by ~2px per row, scoped to ONLY this dialog
  via .appt-modal .form-group / .g2 / .g3 row-gap overrides (Angular's
  default style encapsulation keeps this from affecting .form-group/.g2
  anywhere else in the app)

Appointment dialog — header now shows customer name + DOB:
- When editing an existing appointment, fetches the full Customer
  record (the appointment payload only carries a pre-joined
  customerFullName string, not DOB) and displays 'LastName, FirstName'
  plus DOB next to the 'Edit Appointment' label
- Note: requirement also asked for a middle initial in the name format,
  but no middle name/initial field exists anywhere in this system (not
  in the database schema, backend Customer entity, or frontend Customer
  model) — there is no data to display. Documented in code; straightforward
  to extend once that field is added to the customer record.
